column5: I used to regularly keep an eye on the names, offences, convictions and fines through the M. N. R.'s 'BUSTED' site, but all I now get is #404 NOT FOUND. Does anyone kinow what happened to the site? Is it still out there, or was it a victim of 'budget cuts' like so many others. It was really interesting just how much some of those 'scofflaws' were getting fined for getting caught not obeying our game & fish laws. Does ANYBODY still check this site out or know where it went?

Is this what you are looking for??  http://www.mnr.gov.on.ca/en/Business/Enforcement/2ColumnSubPage/STEL02_164545.html  Seems you can look up prior years there as well.  Nothing showing up past Sept 25 2013....so either they are not posting them anymore or they are just behind in updating.

Yeah h h  h   h . . .   I DID find that much, they're usually up to about 3 -  4  months behind, so it looks like they've diasappeared for good? But . . .   thank-you for checking for me . . . .    I'm brain dead when it comes to computer use . . . .   I just figured may y y y  b   e I had something punched in wrong!
Here you go, Steve. Courtesy of TJ. http://ontariofishingcommunity.com/forums/index.php?showtopic=73241 also here https://www.facebook.com/MNRWatch
